&lt;h1 class="relative group">Integration by part
&lt;div id="integration-by-part" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#integration-by-part" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>当 Integral 内存在两个函数的乘积的时候，可以使用 Integration by parts&lt;/li>
&lt;li>已知有 Derivative&amp;rsquo;s Product Rule&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>$$
\left( u(x) v(x) \right)&amp;rsquo; = u&amp;rsquo;(x) v(x) + u(x) v&amp;rsquo;(x)
$$&lt;/p></description><media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://buezw.github.io/docs/uoft/24/calculus/calculus8.methodsofintegration/feature.png"/></item><item><title>Calculus 9. Series</title><link>https://buezw.github.io/docs/uoft/24/calculus/calculus9.series/</link><pubDate>Wed, 22 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>youremail@example.com (Buezwqwg)</author><guid>https://buezw.github.io/docs/uoft/24/calculus/calculus9.series/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>Last Edit: 1/22/25&lt;/p>
&lt;/blockquote>
&lt;h2 class="relative group">Sequences
&lt;div id="sequences" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#sequences" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Sequence是按照一定顺序排列的一列数。序列可以是有限的也可以是无限的，通常表示为\(a_1, a_2, a_3, \ldots\)，其中\(a_n\)表示序列的第n项&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 class="relative group">Limit of a Sequence
&lt;div id="limit-of-a-sequence" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#limit-of-a-sequence" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h3>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>对于一个Sequence，如果有
$$\lim_{n\rightarrow\infty}a_n=L,L\in \mathbb R$$&lt;/li>
&lt;li>则该Sequence的Limit为L&lt;/li>
&lt;li>如果存在这个L，也可以说Sequence是Converge 收敛的&lt;/li>
&lt;li>如果不存在，则Sequence Diverge 发散&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h4 class="relative group">ex. Nature Number
&lt;div id="ex-nature-number" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#ex-nature-number" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h4>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>找到Sequence \(a_n = \left(1 + \frac{1}{n}\right)^n\)的Limit
$$\lim_{n \to \infty} a_n = \lim_{n \to \infty} \left(1 + \frac{1}{n}\right)^n = e$$&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 class="relative group">Properties of Limits of Sequences
&lt;div id="properties-of-limits-of-sequences" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#properties-of-limits-of-sequences" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h3>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Let \(\lim_{n \to \infty} a_n = L \text{ and } \lim_{n \to \infty} b_n = K\)
$$\lim_{n \to \infty} (a_n \pm b_n) = L \pm K$$
$$\lim_{n \to \infty} c a_n = cL$$
$$\lim_{n \to \infty} (a_n b_n) = LK$$
$$\lim_{n \to \infty} \frac{a_n}{b_n} = \frac{L}{K}$$&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 class="relative group">Squeeze Theorem for Sequences
&lt;div id="squeeze-theorem-for-sequences" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#squeeze-theorem-for-sequences" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h3>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Squeeze Theorem也可以用来解Sequence的Convergence，其通常用在 \((-1)^n, \sin(x)\)等在\(n\rightarrow \infty\)时oscillate的函数中&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h4 class="relative group">ex. Sequence Convergence by Squeeze Theorem
&lt;div id="ex-sequence-convergence-by-squeeze-theorem" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#ex-sequence-convergence-by-squeeze-theorem" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h4>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>证明Sequence \({ c_n } = \left{ (-1)^n \frac{1}{n!} \right}\)收敛&lt;/li>
&lt;li>使用两个序列\(a_n=\frac{1}{2^n}\)，已知Factorial的扩散速度小于Exponential，有
$$-\frac{1}{2^n} \leq (-1)^n \frac{1}{n!} \leq \frac{1}{2^n}, \quad n \geq 4$$&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 class="relative group">Monotonic Sequences
&lt;div id="monotonic-sequences" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#monotonic-sequences" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h3>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>当一个Sequence的每一项都单调递增或单调递减时，该Sequence被称为Monotonic Sequence&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 class="relative group">Bounded Sequence
&lt;div id="bounded-sequence" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#bounded-sequence" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h3>
&lt;h4 class="relative group">Bounded Above
&lt;div id="bounded-above" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#bounded-above" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h4>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>当存在一个\(M\in \mathbb R\)使得\(a_n\leq M\)时，称该Sequence Bounded Above&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h4 class="relative group">Bounded Below
&lt;div id="bounded-below" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#bounded-below" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h4>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>当存在一个\(M\in \mathbb R\)使得\(a_n\geq M\)时，称该Sequence Bounded Below&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h4 class="relative group">Bounded
&lt;div id="bounded" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#bounded" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h4>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>当一个Sequence同时Bounded Above和Below的时候，其Bounded&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 class="relative group">Theorem - Convergent Sequence are Bounded
&lt;div id="theorem---convergent-sequence-are-bounded" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#theorem---convergent-sequence-are-bounded" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h3>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>如果一个Sequence Convergent，则其一定Bounded&lt;/li>
&lt;li>同理也可以反推，如果一个Sequence Bounded并且是Monotonic 单调的Sequence的话，该Sequence Convergent 收敛&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 class="relative group">Series (Infinite Series)
&lt;div id="series-infinite-series" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#series-infinite-series" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>对于Sequence来说，它的所有项相加的和便成为了Series
$$S_n=\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} a_n = a_1 + a_2 + a_3 + \cdots + a_n + \cdots$$&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 class="relative group">Convergent of Series
&lt;div id="convergent-of-series" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#convergent-of-series" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h3>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>对于一个Series \(\sum^\infty_{n=1}a_n\)来说，如果其Partial Sum（前n项之和）等于S，则该Series Converge，反则Diverge&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 class="relative group">Telescoping Series 列项级数
&lt;div id="telescoping-series-%E5%88%97%E9%A1%B9%E7%BA%A7%E6%95%B0" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#telescoping-series-%E5%88%97%E9%A1%B9%E7%BA%A7%E6%95%B0" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h3>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>通过将级数的两个项组合得到一个新的通项公式求得级数的解&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h4 class="relative group">ex. Finding Series Convergency by Telescoping
&lt;div id="ex-finding-series-convergency-by-telescoping" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#ex-finding-series-convergency-by-telescoping" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h4>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>求解\(\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{2}{4n^2 - 1}\)
$$a_n = \frac{2}{4n^2 - 1} = \frac{2}{(2n - 1)(2n + 1)} = \frac{1}{2n - 1} - \frac{1}{2n + 1}$$&lt;/li>
&lt;li>通过观察规律可以看出
$$S_n = \left( \frac{1}{1} - \frac{1}{3} \right) + \left( \frac{1}{3} - \frac{1}{5} \right) + \cdots + \left( \frac{1}{2n-1} - \frac{1}{2n+1} \right) = 1 - \frac{1}{2n+1}$$&lt;/li>
&lt;li>最终得出
$$\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{2}{4n^2 - 1} = \lim_{n \to \infty} S_n = \lim_{n \to \infty} \left(1 - \frac{1}{2n+1}\right) = 1$$&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 class="relative group">Geometric Series
&lt;div id="geometric-series" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#geometric-series" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h3>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>形如\(\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} ar^n\)的Series被称为Geometric Series，其完整形式为
$$\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} ar^n = a + ar + ar^2 + \cdots + ar^n + \cdots, \quad a \neq 0$$&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h4 class="relative group">Convergenvce of Geometric Series
&lt;div id="convergenvce-of-geometric-series" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#convergenvce-of-geometric-series" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h4>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>当Geometric Series的的敛散性高度取决于其公比r的取值&lt;/li>
&lt;li>具体来说当\(0&amp;lt;|r|&amp;lt;1\) Geometric Series Converge ，当\(|r|\geq 1\)，其Diverge&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h4 class="relative group">The Value Geometric Series Converge to
&lt;div id="the-value-geometric-series-converge-to" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#the-value-geometric-series-converge-to" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h4>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Geometric Sereis是很特别的一个Series，于大部分Series不同，当其Converge的时候可以简单的求出Series的值为
$$\lim_{n \to \infty} S_n = \lim_{n \to \infty} \left[ \frac{a(1 - r^n)}{1 - r} \right] = \frac{a}{1 - r} \lim_{n \to \infty} (1 - r^n) = \frac{a}{1 - r}$$&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 class="relative group">Property of Infinite Series
&lt;div id="property-of-infinite-series" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#property-of-infinite-series" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h3>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>如果\(\sum a_n\)和\(\sum b_n\)都是Converge的Series，并且分别收敛到A和B，则有
$$\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} c a_n = cA$$
$$\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} (a_n + b_n) = A + B$$
$$\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} (a_n - b_n) = A - B$$&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 class="relative group">p-Series and Harmonic Series
&lt;div id="p-series-and-harmonic-series" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#p-series-and-harmonic-series" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>$$\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{1}{n^p} = \frac{1}{1^p} + \frac{1}{2^p} + \frac{1}{3^p} + \cdots$$&lt;/p></description><media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://buezw.github.io/docs/uoft/24/calculus/calculus9.series/feature.png"/></item><item><title>Calculus A1. Polynomial Interpolation</title><link>https://buezw.github.io/docs/uoft/24/calculus/calculusa1.polynomialinterpolation/</link><pubDate>Mon, 13 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>youremail@example.com (Buezwqwg)</author><guid>https://buezw.github.io/docs/uoft/24/calculus/calculusa1.polynomialinterpolation/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>Last Edit: 1/13/25&lt;/p>
&lt;/blockquote>
&lt;h1 class="relative group">Polynomial Interpolation
&lt;div id="polynomial-interpolation" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700"
style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#polynomial-interpolation" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>如果想要找一个Polynomial，其穿过两个Point，很简单的做法就是建立$P(x)=ax+b$的多项式&lt;/li>
&lt;li>但是如果问题变成了三个点甚至更多，问题的复杂度就会上升很多，于是需要考虑另一种做法&lt;/li>
&lt;li>对于点$(-1,-1),(1,3),(2,-2)$我们需要找到一个Polynomial穿过这三个点，可以先写出三个Quadratic Polynomial
$$L_1(x) := \begin{cases}
1, &amp;amp; \text{if } x = -1 \
0, &amp;amp; \text{if } x = 1 \
0, &amp;amp; \text{if } x = 2,
\end{cases}&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>L_2(x) := \begin{cases}
0, &amp;amp; \text{if } x = -1 \
1, &amp;amp; \text{if } x = 1 \
0, &amp;amp; \text{if } x = 2,
\end{cases}&lt;/p></description><media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://buezw.github.io/docs/uoft/24/calculus/calculusa1.polynomialinterpolation/feature.png"/></item></channel></rss>